Regardless of his career choice, a person who speaks a second language will benefit from a real benefit to the future through this sustainable competence.
Being able to communicate directly with foreigners will automatically place the multilingual person in front of its competitors.
According to a 2013 YouGov survey of 4,000 adults in the United Kingdom, 75% of them did not master a foreign language to hold a conversation. French was the only language spoken by a two-digit percentage (15%).
