On Saturday, the North Korean Minister of Foreign Affairs told the United Nations that maintaining sanctions strengthened its confidence in the United States and that it would be impossible for his country to unilaterally renounce nuclear weapons in these circumstances.
At the annual General Assembly of the World Organization, Ri Yong Ho stated that North Korea had taken "significant measures of goodwill" last year, such as stopping nuclear and missile tests, dismantling the nuclear test site and its commitment not to proliferate nuclear weapons and technology
