Nevertheless, the tone of Ri's speech was radically different from that of last year, when he had stated before the United Nations General Assembly that it was inevitable to point the North Korean missiles on North American territory after President Trump had qualified Kim as a "male man" on a suicide mission.
Trump, who had threatened the United Nations last year to “completely destroy” North Korea, did not praise this year for the courage with which Kim applied disarmament measures, but added that much remained to be done and that sanctions would not be lifted until North Korea disarmed.
