Addressing the United Nations General Assembly, the Minister for Foreign Affairs, Walid al-Moualem, said that the situation in the country was improving.
"Today, the situation on the ground is more stable and safer thanks to the progress made in the fight against terrorism," he said.
The government continues to rehabilitate the areas destroyed by terrorists in order to restore normality.
All conditions are now met for the voluntary repatriation of refugees to the country that they have been forced to leave because of terrorism and unilateral economic measures aimed at their daily lives and livelihoods.
The United Nations considers that more than 5.5 million Syrians had deserted the country since the war began in 2011.
Six million other people still living in the country need humanitarian assistance.
Al-Moualem said the Syrian regime would welcome aid for the reconstruction of that devastated country.
He stressed, however, that he would not accept conditional assistance or assistance from countries that sponsored the insurrection.
